column3:
<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
Catty is looking over the food stores, her face a mask of concern.
Slay two whiptails, then defeat the enraged Jaculus.
This should be enough to last us. At least until those scaly buggers are taken care of...
These days it seems there're more pests than people living in Stilltide, what with all the hopefuls running off to Eulmore.

Those flying lizards are the worst of the lot, though. You can't even leave for an honest day's work anymore without a swarm of them flapping sky demons nipping at your heels from here to Governor's Row.
And don't get me started on their leader! “Jaculus,” we call him. With the way that vicious blighter comes after you, you'd think he bloody owns the place!
Ugh, <Emphasis>someone</Emphasis> needs to topple that little tyrant. None of us fancy losing a finger, but maybe you're up to the challenge?
If you're keen to draw him out, just skewer a couple of his broodmates. That'll get his attention soon enough.
Did you say you were going to gut that territorial lizard leader for us? Like I said, just murder some of his mates, and you'll soon get an audience with Jaculus himself.
You got the bitey little bastard, then!? Shadows be praised! Now maybe we can work the fields in peace.
If you hadn't done the deed, I was afraid we'd start running out of food. And I've no wish to watch anyone starve to death...
Aye, I know we could move to Gatetown and live on handouts of meol like the rest of them, but we have our pride.
It's not like we could just move to Gatetown and live on handouts of meol anymore. Did you know that stuff was the flesh of sin eaters? <shudder> No bloody thank you.
If there's any choice in the matter, we'd rather take care of our own needs while we can...with a little help from battle-savvy travelers such as yourself, of course!
